        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 7:19PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 719 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marlette, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sandusky, Marlette, Deckerville, Port Sanilac, Carsonville,
Applegate, Watertown, Elmer, Forester, McGregor, Snover, Juhl,
Decker, and Richmondville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
